[[span class="moo"]]Moosphere[[/span]]'s mass neurological advertisement campaign connects to a chain of legitimate products -- both real and dream-based -- produced by the human subconscious and esoteric sources. A significant sum of [[span class="moo"]]Moosphere[[/span]] products come from the neural and memetic pathways of its market base.

[[span class="moo"]]Moosphere[[/span]] ectoentropically generates 31% of its flagship product, [[span class="moo"]]Mind-Milk™[[/span]], from the hypothalamus and pineal gland (hormone release centers) respectively, while a metaphysical source secretes the remaining 69%. Regular consumers of [[span class="moo"]]Moosphere[[/span]] products develop milk curdle build-up on portions of cerebral tissue, which further influences consumers to use [[span class="moo"]]Moosphere[[/span]] products but does not otherwise negatively affect their health.

